cs.CR, cs.SE, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.PL

This paper is likely to belong to the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-category as it deals with malware analysis and lineage, which are important topics in the field of cybersecurity. It could also belong to cs.SE (Software Engineering) as it proposes a novel approach for identifying versions of a malware family and a scalable code indexing technique. Additionally, the paper uses machine learning techniques to analyze malware samples, which could place it in the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. The paper also involves graph theory and algorithms, which could make it relevant to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a technique for identifying shared functions between input samples, which could place it in the cs.PL (Programming Languages) sub-category.
